  <h1 id="title"> Michael Franzese</h1>
  <p id="subtitle">"The Yuppy Don"</p>
  <figure id="img-div">
    <img id="image"  src= "https://news.psu.edu/sites/default/files/styles/photo_gallery_large/public/MichaelFranzese-News.jpg?itok=VydFFZux" alt="Michael Franzese" />
  <figcaption id= "img-caption"> Michael Franzese "The Yuppy Don" </figcaption></figure> 
<section id="tribute-info"> 
  <h2 id="Headline"> Here is a timeline of the dons life:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>1951</strong> - Michael was born in Brooklyn, New York, United States.</li>
    <li><strong>1969</strong> - After finishing high school Michael entered a pre-med program at <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hofstra_University" target="_blank"> Hofstra University.</a></li>
    <li><strong>1971</strong> - Micahel dropped out of college to help his family financially as his father <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Franzese" target="_blank"> Sonny Franzese</a></li>
    <li><strong>1975</strong>- On haloween night micahel was inducted into the <a  href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombo_crime_family" target="_blank">Columbo Crime Family</a> and was offically a "Made man".</li>
    <li><strong>1980</strong> - Micahel started his bootleg gasoline company and made a average of $8 million per week</li>
    <li><strong>1984</strong> - The don met his while Camille on one of his production sets.</li>
    <li><strong>1985</strong> - Micahel was acquitted on racketeering charges. Later the same year he was indicted on 14 counts of racketeering, counterfeiting and extortion from the gasoline bootlet racket.</li>
    <li><strong>1986</strong> - Michael pleaded guily to one count of racketeering conspiricy and one count of tax conspiricy. He was sentenced to 10 years in federal prison and ordered to pay over $14 million in restitution. </li> 
      <li><strong>1989</strong> - Michael was released from prision after 43 months.</li>
    <li><strong>1991</strong> - Micahel was then put back to prison and sentenced to four years for violating his probation requirements.</li>
    <li><strong>1991</strong> - While serving his time Michael become a born again christian and found God after he was given a bible by one of the prison guards</li>
    <li><strong>1994</strong> - Michael was released from prison</li> 
    <li><strong>1994</strong> - Since his release Micahel has become a motivation speaker and encourages young kids and inmates to change their live away from crime and sin.</li> 
    </ul>
  <blockquote cite ="https://www.azquotes.com/author/37817-Michael_Franzese">
<p id="Quote">"God has a purpose and plan for your life and nothing can stand in the way of it - except you. Are you ready to listen? It's time to stand up and be bold for Jesus." </p>
    <cite id= "quote words"> -- Michael Franzese</cite> </blockquote> 
